{"tid":1948524,"cid":15,"subCid":0,"title":"美國開始出現負油價","createTime":"2020-03-29T05:28:43.000Z","updateTime":"2020-03-30T16:18:16.000Z","uid":54870,"like":45,"dislike":1,"uniUserReply":70,"replies":[{"pid":"afd868cc298fd63dcbf43a7fdaaa63a7efbf29a0","tid":1948524,"uid":54870,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-29T05:28:43.000Z","msg":"據Bloomberg報導，一種工業用的重油Wyoming Asphalt Sour，市價為負19美仙，即是生產商倒貼買家。<br />\n負價格原因：經濟近乎停頓，儲油設備存滿。<br />\n事實上，極多內陸油價標的，價格之低，令業外人士咋舌 - Canadian Western Select 做價$5.06美元(下同)，Oklahoma Sour跌至$5.75，Nebraska Intermediate$8，Wyoming Sweet承惠$3。<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-27/one-corner-of-u-s-oil-market-has-already-seen-negative-prices\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2020-03-27%2Fone-corner-of-u-s-oil-market-has-already-seen-negative-prices&d=XV0%2F%2BsWk6HIEEz5%2BsPHJewsTF5hDypdTwPi8eTnvKzQ%3D&h=33aba2ed\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-03-27/one-corner-of-u-s-oil-market-has-already-seen-negative-prices</a><br />\n<br />\nIn an obscure corner of the American physical oil market, crude prices have turned negative -- producers are actually paying consumers to take away the black stuff.<br />\n<br />\nThe first crude stream to turn upside down was Wyoming Asphalt Sour, a dense oil used mostly to produce paving bitumen. Mercuria Energy Group Ltd., a trading house, bid negative 19 cents per barrel in mid-March for the crude, effectively asking producers to pay for the luxury of getting rid of their output.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;These are landlocked crude with just no buyers,&rdquo; said Elisabeth Murphy, an analyst at consultant ESAI Energy. &ldquo;In areas where storage is filling up quickly, prices could go negative. Shut-ins are likely to happen by then.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nBrent and West Texas Intermediate, the benchmarks closely followed in Wall Street, are hovering above $20 a barrel. But in the world of physical oil -- where actual barrels change hands -- producers are getting much less as demand plunges due to the lockdown to contain the spread of the coronavirus.<br />\n<br />\nOil traders believe other crude streams are likely to see negative prices soon at the well-head as refiners reduce the amount of crude they process, leaving some landlocked crude without easy access to pipeline trapped.<br />\n<br />\nSeveral crude grades in North American are already trading inside the single digit territory as the market tries to force some output to shut-in. Canadian Western Select, the benchmark price for the giant oil-sands industry in Canada, fell to $5.06 a barrel on Friday. Southern Green Canyon in the Gulf of Mexico is worth $11.51 a barrel, Oklahoma Sour is changing hands at $5.75, Nebraska Intermediate at $8, while Wyoming Sweet prices at $3 a barrel."},{"pid":"60cc5b7ce6f9a42b589e124a08d3714e2704032a","tid":1948524,"uid":54870,"like":112,"dislike":2,"score":110,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-03-29T05:43:35.000Z","msg":"<span style=\"color: red;\"><del>Drop to zero</del></span><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/no.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/no.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/no.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/no.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\nDrop to negative<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/good.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fc23516ca388529d7a9687b51a531486867d4e93","tid":1948524,"uid":189157,"like":91,"dislike":8,"score":83,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2020-03-29T05:45:05.000Z","msg":"負油價<br />\n負利率<br />\n負股價<br />\n負人工<br />\n負樓價<br />\n<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/jable.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"bc6b70c7110e6421969c1aa7f8c072e486c2140c","